==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tenaille
<hw>Te*naille"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., a pair of
pincers or tongs, a tenaille, fr. L. <ets>tenaculum</ets>. See
<er>Tenaculum</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>An outwork in the
main ditch, in front of the curtain, between two bastions. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Ravelin</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tenaillon</ent>⟦br⟧
